The paper discusses the use of machine learning models in conversational AI agents, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of self-learning and collaborative filtering mechanisms, which are common in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) research, making cs.AI the second most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed system, which is a common concern in large-scale ML systems, making cs.LG the third most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of anonymized data and user feedback, which raises issues related to privacy and human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.SD and cs.HC the fourth and fifth most likely sub-categories, respectively.
